    }

If for some reason, you want to achieve this by editing `BillsDto` only, then you can implement a custom serializer for `UserDto` and apply it by making use of the `@JsonSerialize`. But to ensure that you&#39;re not disclosing the sensitive data somewhere, it would be better to apply this policy in one place - in the `UserDto`, because you or one of your colleagues might simply forget to `@JsonSerialize` in some of the classes which uses `UserDto`.

