	return new InMemoryUserDetailsManager(demo);
}
```

I&#39;m not sure right now, but maybe the password should be `{noop}demo` to tell the `PasswordEncoder` bean that the password is not encoded. Remember that a noop password encoder should only be used for demo purposes.


